edbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tsv1665702739177.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsv1665702739177.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tsv1665702739177.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tsv1665702739177\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /delacc\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Delete a Uniface Router or Uniface Server account on Windows platforms.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__section_w2220ab1b5b1_w2221ab1b5_w2222ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__p_d148703e1_d148704e1_d148705e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/delacc</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AccountName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__section_w2223ab1b5b3_w2224ab1b5_w2225ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d351241e63\">\n                  \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__p_d148709e1_d148710e1_d148711e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AccountName</var>—name of the account to be deleted.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__section_w2226ab1b5b5_w2227ab1b5_w2228ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d351241e75\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__p_d148715e1_d148716e1_d148717e1\">Use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/delacc</span> to delete an account. This is required if you want to change the password of an existing account; for example, if you want to change the password of the default <code class=\"ph codeph\">urouter</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">UnifaceServer</code>, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">userver</code> accounts.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tsv1665702739177__p_d148718e1_d148719e1_d148720e1\">In this case, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/delacc</span> to remove the account, and then recreate it with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/newacc</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/passwd</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fvp1665702738973.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/newacc</a><p>Create a new account on Windows platforms for the Uniface Router or Uniface Server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tfr1665702739041.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/passwd</a><p>Creates a password for the newly created Uniface Server or Uniface Router account.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qzj1665702739109.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Manually Creating and Deleting Uniface Router and Server Accounts</a><p>If the installer was unable to create accounts for the Uniface Server and Uniface Router on Microsoft Windows, you can manually create these accounts.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/delacc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /delacc Delete a Uniface Router or Uniface Server account on Windows platforms. /delacc AccountName Parameters AccountName —name of the account to be deleted. Description Use /delacc to delete an account. This is required if you want to change the password of an existing account; for example, if you want to change the password of the default urouter , UnifaceServer , or userver accounts. In this case, use /delacc to remove the account, and then recreate it with /newacc and /passwd . Related Links /newacc Create a new account on Windows platforms for the Uniface Router or Uniface Server. /passwd Creates a password for the newly created Uniface Server or Uniface Router account. Manually Creating and Deleting Uniface Router and Server Accounts If the installer was unable to create accounts for the Uniface Server and Uniface Router on Microsoft Windows, you can manually create these accounts. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}